-- Mexico Stocks: Penoles, Grupo Mexico, Urbi Shares Were Active
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-05-09T20:59:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-09/mexico-stocks-penoles-grupo-mexico-urbi-shares-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close in Mexico City.  The IPC index fell 0.2 percent to 39,122.82.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), a Mexican miner of
silver and gold, fell 2.7 percent to 592.08 pesos. The metals
tumbled on concern political turmoil in  Greece  is deepening.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB)  , Mexico’s biggest mining
company, fell 1.5 percent to 39.88 pesos. Copper futures
retreated as European concern hurt prospects for demand.  Urbi Desarrollos Urbanos SAB (URBI*)  , Mexico’s third-
biggest homebuilder by sales, slid 2.3 percent to 12.71 pesos.
Urbi may lose its place on  MSCI Inc. (MSCI) ’s index of Latin American
companies in a rebalancing set to be announced May 15,  Banco
Santander SA (SAN)  said in an April 27 report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
